{
  "texts": [
    "As shown in Fig. 18 (in appendix), this area is growing.",
    "We observed that there is an increase in studies published on the use of TM techniques to distil information from the medical records/electronic health records.",
    "Topic 4 accounts for 1.84% of the entire document.",
    "In this category, prior studies evidence that TM techniques were used to perform key tasks such as identifying events that impact stock market price from the financial market news (Liu 2020; Mahajan et al. 2008), mining events in a crowded scene (Rodriguez et al. 2009) or video (Hendel et al. 2010; Hospedales et al. 2009; Shirahama and Uehara 2008), tracking web video topics (Cao et al. 2011), detecting irregular behaviours in video scene (Park and Yoo 2012), motion pattern detection (Zhou et al. 2019), traffic patterns detection (Ahmadi et al. 2018; Wang 2023), fake news video detection (Choi and Ko 2021) and activity routine discovery (Seiter et al. 2015).",
    "As shown in Fig. 19 (in appendix), reasonable number of papers were published in this area across the years especially in 2018."
  ]
}